<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Spawrhawk on 02-07-2002 12:27 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">     Honestly, the cleric class really has no issues to speak of.  All of them for the most part have been addressed and either fixed or given an explanation as to why we would never see an ability (i.e. invisability).

     Pre 50 we are healers.  Post 50 we are damn good healers.  Look at some other classes and you will see that we have little to complain about (i.e. Necros, Mages).  I really hope Verant fixes the caster vs. melee issue soon.  But with the coming implementation of the Legends server, I just see them postponing any work on the other servers.  /shrug

     I would love it if invis potions were stackable though.  If they can make sow potions stackable, I'm sure they can code it so that a shaman can combine 10 in his lil pouch and make a stackable invis potion. 

     And I was waiting on who would bring up Ragefire.  /chuckle I really don't see this as a nerf but an honest attempt at atuning the mob to be more in line with other epic mob hunts.  I rather this version of Ragefire than the other.  Why?  Because I know that I don't have to fear being ganked or steamrolled over when I hand in my pearl.  The changes were only so that the grief associated with the spawn would be reduced and also all your work for your epic not be totally lost.  But I'm rambling.  

     Out of all my toons, my cleric has the least issues.  :)

Spawrhawk Wormwood
59 Templar of Fennin Ro</TEXTAREA>
